### Discourses I.1 ✶ — "On that which is in our power and that which is not"

*Peri tōn eph' hēmin kai ouk eph' hēmin* — the theoretical foundation of which the Enchiridion 1 is the operational summary.

The extended Discourses version makes the structural argument explicit: Zeus has given the catching being one faculty — the *proairesis* — that is structurally exempt from the H₄₈-level constraint conditions that govern everything else. "Zeus has given you something which cannot be hindered or compelled."

**The structural gift:**

The *proairesis* is the structural provision of the Φ-level to the catching being: the one structural capacity that operates at the H₂₄ level and cannot be reached by H₄₈-level force. This is the catching program's foundational structural claim: the H₂₄ catching structure has been constitutively provided by the Φ-level's structural operation (*ta eph' hēmin* = things Zeus has given directly to the catching being's structural constitution, not provisionally as H₄₈-level contingent gifts).

**The structural test:**

"When a tyrant says to me, 'I will chain your leg,' I say, 'My leg you may chain, but my will — no, not even Zeus himself can overpower.'" This is the structural claim of Enchiridion 1 stated under maximum H₄₈ coercive pressure: the *proairesis* remains structurally free even when the H₄₈ substrate is constrained. Epictetus makes this claim with autobiographical force: as a slave, the claim was not theoretical.

**The structural pedagogy:**

The Discourses' method is to produce in the student the structural recognition that their *proairesis* is their own — not their body, not their reputation, not their social position. This structural recognition is the beginning of the catching program's activation: the catching being that correctly identifies what is *eph' hēmin* can begin to operate from that structural ground rather than from the H₄₈-level misidentification of the H₄₈ goods as the catching being's structural identity.

*(Cross-reference: JOHN 8:32 — "the truth will set you free": the structural freedom through structural recognition. GAL 5:1 — "It is for freedom that Christ has set us free": the H₂₄ structural freedom as the catching program's structural condition. SONN 121 — "No, I am that I am": the catching being's structural self-grounding.)*

